      <section eId="sec_27_2701">
        <num>27-2701</num>
        <heading>Definitions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2701__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a bag made of cloth or other machine washable fabric that has\nhandles; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2701__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a durable plastic bag with handles that is specifically designed\nand manufactured for multiple reuse.\n  6. "Store" means a retail establishment that provides plastic carryout\nbags to its customers as a result of the sale of a product and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2701__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>has\nover ten thousand square feet of retail space, or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_2701__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>such retail\nestablishment is part of a chain engaged in the same general field of\nbusiness which operates five or more units of over five thousand square\nfeet of retail space in this state under common ownership and\nmanagement.\n  7. "Film plastic" means uncontaminated non-rigid film plastic\npackaging products composed of plastic resins, which include, but are\nnot limited to, newspaper bags, dry cleaning bags and shrink-wrap.\n  * NB There are 2 ยง 27-2701's\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
